Defendant in custody.    
Count 2 - Deliver Methamphetamine as repeater with use of dangerous weapon, 2nd or subsequent offense - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of six (6) years, three (3) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision, consecutive to sentence serving on 06 CF 430;
Count 3 - Possess firearm by felon - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three (3) years, one (1) year initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision, consecutive to count 2;
Count 6 - Fleeing an officer - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of two (2) years, one (1) year initial confinement, followed by one (1) year extended supervision, consecutive to counts 2 and 3.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision on count 2 are:
1) Repay $495.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
2) Pay court costs;
3) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Have no contact with any known drug users or dealers;
6) Submit to random urine screns and pay for same;
7) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
8) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process.
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.   
Minutes.
